annotation.TEXT: Well, I guess I'll have to wait until the RNG sends a bullet my way to kill me, or time runs out... I'll skip to when one of those things is about to happen.
DOMINATING!
Space-time rewind count: 17
Let's do some IDCLIP-ing!
Yep, it reset the level. I guess I'll show you guys the power up causing Lakitu to instantly toss an extra spiny egg again.

Yeah, I kept going there off camera, and it's endless (at least until I timed out), just as if I jumped over a flagpole in most cases. So, I'm going to just go down this pipe and return to the level... or not. Looks like I'm stuck here since the pipe exits here aren't set for world 1 (probably worlds 3 and 6).
Demo count: 30
Space-time rewind count: 18
Yay, I'm back to my burninating power level!

WHAT THE HECK?! Umm... Yeah, I've seen this happen before when using a Game Genie code to change underground bricks into coins (XKSOZL). When Mario collects 3 coins in the same vertical column simultaneously, the game might freak out like this for whatever reason.
Nuts. The 1-up trick won't work in this instance, as the koopa is too far to the left on the step it's on, but if I go down a couple steps and wait for it to wake up, I can try again.
Some points of 24 lost.
Alright, now for 1-D, which will be the same as 4-1, aside from the pipe exits, of course.
HIYOOOO!!!
1-C is 3-4, and just like most castles, there's a way onto the roof. This springboard near the start seems like it should get me up there, but I always fall short.
...Or until I enter an infinite expanse of emptiness. One moment, please...
Regret, didn't catch!
And there's the pipe that I emerged from the first time around, so we've seen all of 4-1 now.
Now, I wonder if this flagpole exit will halt the game if I'd get fireworks...
Okay, let's stay away from that pipe that's no good to me. Man, I just can't stop finding more and more strange problems with this hack...
Now for 1-A, which should be the same as 3-2, the short level with the stars and Hammer Bros., and there are no pipe exits here, so I'll just rush through it again, just like last time.
Time for 1-E, which is exactly like 4-2, except for the pipe exits, of course.
Weren't there two Toads here last time? (Darn you, sprite limit.) Anyway, I should be able to get onto the roof here.
1-B is the same as 3-3, but I'm going to do this level differently this time!
...Yay! I can go on to world 1-9! Of course, this is going to be the same as 3-1, but with the pipe and vine exits resetting the level as usual.
I'm assuming both of these pipes will return me to the main area, but I'm going to keep going until the screen stops scrolling...
KILLING SPREE!
Well, looks like the RNG won that race!
Whoa, there was a freaky flame, but it missed me. Of course, even if it had hit me, I would've been fine, due to the star.
Too bad there was only 17 enemies in this level, so I couldn't get up to UNSTOPPABLE or GODLIKE. Oh, well.
I wonder if Mario's eating TPP's favorite food (Omelets4&) in that castle?
Ah, it turns into a red koopa (which would probably walk off ledges if I let it).
Painfully.

Here's something interesting that I don't think I ever pointed out before. When there's a Lakitu present, and you're not already at the enemy sprite limit, Lakitu will toss an extra spiny egg the instant you grab a power up for some reason.
Blew it again. Well, screw it. I'm outta here!
I guess that spiny can live.
BLASTOISE PUNCH!!!
Whoa, you sure respawned quickly this time. Here, have a fireball.
Nuts, I thought I'd get the 6 there, but I just missed. Oh, well. I'm not gonna go back in time just to see if trying for fireworks would halt the game here.

Oh, what? There was a world 1 pipe exit there? Well, no wonder I kept being sent to the warp zone area no matter which pipe I took back in 4-2 several episodes ago! The intended pipe exit for the underground bonus room was set to world 1 instead of world 4!
I don't know why the game does that, but whatever. Just stay alert.
Yeah, I figured there was a second hidden block.
What happens if I stomp this glitchy thing over here instead of frying it?
Oh, and here's a sneak peek of world 1-F, just for the heck of it. To be continued...
Demo count: 31
Whoa, what's this? So, this is where that sky bonus area I couldn't find before was! The exit pointer to it must've been set to world 1 instead of world 3. COINS!!!
Yep, just like that. The pipes are looking for a world 3 pointer, but since the game still thinks I'm in world 1, they'll just reset the level.

Okay, now this time, I'll take the top route, and not just go and jump to my death like I did in 4-1 several episodes ago. Instead, I'll carefully reveal the hidden blocks and use them to get over the wall.
Well, I think I'm gonna call it a day here. Next time, I'll resume with world 1-F, which'll be just like 4-3!
How high will I be able to get the right digit of the world number? We'll find out eventually!
Whoo, just dodged a bullet there. But, of course, the pipe resets the level.
Hmm... I think I'll enter the next enterable pipe to reset the level so that I can fully power up again.
HIYOOOO!!!
That's okay. There are more places where I can get onto the roof, if I'm super. Fortunately, there's a star early on that'll protect me from the flying cheepos.
L-L-LUDICROUS L-L-LAG!!! And, yeah, the status bar will stutter like that when there's lag like this in SMB.
RAMPAGE!
Aw, nuts. Sometimes the game freaks out so much with this kind of coin collecting that it actually crashes completely. Un momento, por favor...
Whoa, I haven't seen this place before. I guess this is where the 1-1 bonus room exit takes me if I don't tour all of the bonus areas at once.
Wait, why am I going this way? I can IDCLIP through the dead end wall here, but then I'll enter the pipe...
Yeah, that was an epic fail on my part.
Note: If there wasn't also an elevator just to the right of me there, I would've been shoved to the right as I was passing through the blocks.
Oh, yeah. Here's me doing the IDCLIP thing with a down elevator.
DOUBLE KILL!

Now, I could just avoid pipe/vine exits for the most part, but I'd still like to try them at least once in each level that has one, in case there actually is a world 1 pointer for some reason (like that pipe at the beginning of 1-6 that still worked).
Demo count: 32
Ow, that sucked. Well, whatever.
Oh, and I recognize this part. This is where that pipe at the beginning of 2-2, 7-2, and 1-6 took me.
Oh, yeah. This split path. I'll first take the lower path to see if the pipe down there resets the level...
Ow, dang bullet... Wait, did that seriously just happen?! LOL!
Hey there, Bullet Bills. How's it going?
Whoa, I'm kind of close to the right edge of the screen here. I'm going to try to center the camera.
And that was an epic fail on the level designer's part. However, I'm not stuck in this case, as I can jump left to land safely after spawning.
Whoa, if I hadn't held A there, I would've fallen through these blocks and to my death again.
LOL, jump fail. At least I still got the six fireworks, though!

Hello, and welcome back to New Strange Mario Bros.! Now, I'm not sure why, but I think the game was halted here last time because the fireworks I was supposed to get just simply couldn't spawn for some reason. However, if I intentionally avoid getting fireworks...
